# Style Macro

The `style` macro runs at build time and returns a class name that applies Spectrum 2 design tokens (colors, spacing, sizing, typography, etc.). It supports a constrained set of values per property that conform to Spectrum 2.

The macro generates atomic CSS classes, keeping your bundle small and scaling well as your app grows. Each property/value pair is emitted once and reused everywhere.

```typescript
import { style } from '@react-spectrum/s2/style' with { type: 'macro' };

<div className={style({ backgroundColor: 'red-400', color: 'white' })}>
  {/* ... */}
</div>
```

Colocating styles with your component code means:

- Develop more efficiently â€“ no switching files or writing selectors
- Refactor with confidence â€“ changes are isolated; deleting a component removes its styles

